message: Undid revision 1211421714 by [[Special:Contributions/Fitzkarl|Fitzkarl]] ([[User talk:Fitzkarl|talk]] He has not been appointed to the Privy Council and is not in the PC register: https://privycouncil.independent.gov.uk/privy-council/privy-council-members/#c)
Title corrected as per my previous edit

The article must refer to his professional title rather than his previous name. There is no other exception, so far as can be seen, for any other peer not to be referred professionally (which the Foreign Secretary article is) by their title. It is disrespectful not to have their title displayed if they have been raised to the peerage. Indeed, not having his title displayed suggests that he is just a random person notwithstanding his obvious history. The title therefore remains to be displayed.

message: It has not been announced by No10 that King Charles has conferred a peerage upon him. There is no gazette of the peerage on the Government's website and the article cannot say he is a baron when he is not until it has been formally announced properly by No10: https://www.gov.uk/search/news-and-communications. People should refrain from having a text war on the title until it is actually announced by the Government.

The House of Lords have announced that he will be raised to the peerage which is a more reliable source, however it remains to be confirmed by the Government and the exact title remains to be confirmed: https://lordslibrary.parliament.uk/peerages-awarded-to-former-prime-ministers/
